name: Api\Objects\Throttling
description: See the object that wraps the throttling information that's returned for the Create an Article and Update an Article endpoints.

properties.name: estimatedDelayInSeconds
properties.description: Estimate of the number of seconds until this request begins processing.

properties.name: isThrottled
properties.description: A Boolean value that indicates whether requests to this channel are currently being throttled. If true, the server adds this request to the queue to process later rather than immediately.

properties.name: queueSize
properties.description: The number of requests currently queued for later processing.

properties.name: quotaAvailable
properties.description: The number of additional article publish or update requests that you can submit now, before the system begins throttling.
